-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Drake & Scull of U.A.E., Kuwait’s NMTC
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-02-16T10:32:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/persian-gulf-stocks-drake-scull-of-u-a-e-kuwait-s-nmtc.html
Dubai’s benchmark  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
fell 0.5 percent to 1,516.05 at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate,
trimming its gain this week to 2 percent. Kuwait’s measure
gained 0.3 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols follow company names.  Drake & Scull International  (DSI UH) advanced as much as
1.3 percent to 95.5 fils, before paring gains to close at 94.2
fils. The Dubai-based construction company expects revenue and
profit this year to grow between 20 percent to 25 percent, Al
Bayan newspaper reported, citing Chief Executive Officer
Khaldoun Tabari.  National Mobile Telecommunications Co. (NMTC)   climbed 2
percent to 2,040 fils. The Kuwaiti mobile-telephone company said
fourth-quarter profit surged 57 percent to 38.2 million dinars
($137 million.)  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
